---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TagList from "../components/TagList.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Dylan" description="About me, my skills, and what I'm working on.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-punctuation)] mb-6">
      ~/portfolio/<span class="text-[var(--color-string)]">about</span>
    </p>

    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-function)] mb-3">About Me</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-comment)] mb-10">
      <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]">// </span>Software engineer, problem solver, outdoor enthusiast
    </p>

    <div class="prose mb-12">
      <p>
        Hi! My name is Dylan Coon and I am from Erie, Pennsylvania. I'm a software engineer
        with a strong foundation in computer science and a passion for solving complex problems.
        I graduated from Penn State University with a degree in Computer Science and a minor in
        Mathematics, where I built a deep understanding of algorithms, systems, and logical
        thinking — skills I apply daily in my work and personal projects. I am proficient in
        Go, Python, C and familiar with Javascript. I have worked with GCP quite a bit as well
        as AWS on occasion. I am always eager to learn new languages and tools.
      </p>

      <p>
        I started my career as an intern at Iron Mountain — an information management company
        known for their cloud based solutions they provide to hundreds of clients globally. As
        an intern, I worked on a ML team that specialized in model optimization and refactoring
        for intelligent document processing. I wrote Python code to extract signatures from
        documents and structure training data in a concurrent manner using a threading library.
        Currently, I'm a software engineer at the company, where I work on an application
        support team. I spend most of my time leveraging my Python skills to automate workflows,
        gather metrics, and monitor cloud environments. I also help validate new releases in
        production. I enjoy working with data, writing clean APIs, and diving into technical
        challenges. My main interests lie in backend development and machine learning.
      </p>

      <p>
        Outside of work, I'm an electronics hobbyist — I enjoy building things on breadboards
        and working with microcontrollers like Arduino and ESP32. I also love diving into
        personal programming projects: I've built a CHIP-8 emulator in C++, an in-memory
        key-value store in Go, and a real-time collaborative editing app with React and
        WebSockets. These side projects let me explore areas like low-level systems programming
        and database internals that I find endlessly interesting.
      </p>

      <p>
        When I'm away from a screen, I like to be outside and spend time with my dog Yankee.
        I am also an avid rock climber — I love the mental and physical puzzle that each climb
        presents. It's a great complement to my love of problem-solving in software.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-sm text-[var(--color-comment)] mb-4">
        <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]">// </span>skills
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
        <div>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-keyword)]">languages</span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]"> — </span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-string)]">Go, Python, C, C++, Javascript</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-keyword)]">cloud</span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]"> — </span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-string)]">GCP, AWS</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-keyword)]">electronics</span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]"> — </span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-string)]">Breadboard prototyping, Arduino, ESP32</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-keyword)]">interests</span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]"> — </span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-string)]">Backend development, machine learning</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-keyword)]">education</span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]"> — </span>
          <span class="text-[var(--color-string)]">Penn State University — B.S. Computer Science, Minor in Mathematics</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-sm text-[var(--color-comment)] mb-4">
        <span class="text-[var(--color-punctuation)]">// </span>this site
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-operator)]">
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build" class="text-[var(--color-constant)] hover:underline">Astro</a> and
        <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" class="text-[var(--color-constant)] hover:underline">Tailwind CSS</a>.
        Deployed on Cloudflare Pages. Content authored in Markdown.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex gap-3">
      <a
        href="https://github.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="px-4 py-2 rounded text-sm border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-punctuation)] hover:border-[var(--color-keyword)] hover:text-[var(--color-keyword)] transition-colors"
      >
        github
      </a>
      <a
        href="mailto:hello@example.com"
        class="px-4 py-2 rounded text-sm border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-punctuation)] hover:border-[var(--color-keyword)] hover:text-[var(--color-keyword)] transition-colors"
      >
        email
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
